---
title: Beef Taco Loaded Potatoes with Peppers, Tomato, and Sour Cream
description: Talk about the best of both worlds: these spuds are one part loaded potato and one part taco fillings, which adds up to a food mashup that’s as genius as it is tasty. The most brilliant part of it might be where our chefs decided to skip the lengthy roasting usually used to make potatoes tender. Instead, they decided to zap them in the microwave to produce the same results in minutes. When the taters are filled with spiced ground beef, peppers, sour cream, and cheese, it’s pretty clear that this combo was truly meant to be.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/beef-taco-loaded-potatoes-35d102a5.jpg
